tledetail"><div class="container w-container"><div class="newsauthortitlewrap"><div data-w-id="01b3f6d6-5ad1-9beb-0111-0084fa078a4b" style="opacity:0" class="newsdetaildate">June 18, 2024</div><div class="text-block-54">-<br/><br/>‍</div><div data-w-id="01b3f6d6-5ad1-9beb-0111-0084fa078a51" style="opacity:0" class="text-block-47">Careers</div></div><div data-w-id="bb2416ea-b75b-5007-394a-f3930a9bbfad" style="opacity:0" class="newstitlewrap"><h2 class="heading-30">HQLAᵡ  IT Ops Engineer</h2></div></div></div><div class="newsmaincontentwrapper"><div class="container w-container"><div class="newsimagewrap w-condition-invisible"><img class="newsdetailimage" src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64747c98fea71f3468e90c67/6672e8c63dbaa6bd3e8eb948_66618c458a7d72540684c765_news.png" alt="" style="opacity:0" sizes="(max-width: 479px) 83vw, (max-width: 991px) 90vw, 89vw" data-w-id="9609d12d-7837-be90-587e-70515287f89b" loading="lazy" srcset="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64747c98fea71f3468e90c67/6672e8c63dbaa6bd3e8eb948_66618c458a7d72540684c765_news-p-500.png 500w, https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64747c98fea71f3468e90c67/6672e8c63dbaa6bd3e8eb948_66618c458a7d72540684c765_news-p-800.png 800w, https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64747c98fea71f3468e90c67/6672e8c63dbaa6bd3e8eb948_66618c458a7d72540684c765_news-p-1080.png 1080w, https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64747c98fea71f3468e90c67/6672e8c63dbaa6bd3e8eb948_66618c458a7d72540684c765_news-p-1600.png 1600w, https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64747c98fea71f3468e90c67/6672e8c63dbaa6bd3e8eb948_66618c458a7d72540684c765_news.png 1988w"/></div><div data-w-id="2c9cdd39-d284-1d0c-da4b-f2885dcb1e6b" style="opacity:0" class="newssourcewrap"><div class="text-block-48">Source: XXX</div></div><div class="newsdetailcontent"><div class="w-row"><div data-w-id="af316dcc-bb16-cc8c-8cfe-3df35b7fb2ac" style="opacity:0" class="column-23 w-col w-col-3"></div><div data-w-id="af316dcc-bb16-cc8c-8cfe-3df35b7fb2cb" style="opacity:0" class="column-20 w-col w-col-9"><div class="newsummary"><p class="newsfirstpara w-dyn-bind-empty"></p><div class="text-block-55 w-dyn-bind-empty"></div><div class="rich-text-block-2 w-richtext"><h3>About HQLAᵡ</h3><p>‍<br/>HQLAᵡ is an innovative financial technology firm that leverages distributed ledger technology (DLT) to bring game-changing efficiencies to the securities finance and repo industry.<br/>Our core clients are banks and asset managers active in the global securities finance and repo markets, and our unique platform enables market participants to execute frictionless, precise and real-time transfer of ownership of securities. This provides our clients with capital cost savings by reducing credit risk, intra-day liquidity requirements and operational risk.<br/>To reinforce our Technology team we are looking for a motivated Ops Engineer. HQLAᵡ has offices in Luxembourg, Zug (Switzerland) and London (UK). This opportunity exists in Luxembourg.</p><h3>Responsibilities</h3><p>‍<br/>• Participate in the daily IT operations of the production platform such as monitoring, security management, change management and incident management.<br/>• Design and maintain a highly reliable and secure production environment, including logging, monitoring, analytics, etc.<br/>• Write and maintain documentation about the HQLAX platform and the systems supporting it.<br/>• Maintain and enhance the Continuous Integration environment for the HQLAX software platform.<br/>• Coordinate the rollout of new releases across all nodes of the HQLAX Corda Business Network.<br/>• Hands-on development and fixing of key components of the HQLAX collateral exchange platform.<br/>• Investigate and resolve incidents.<br/>• Engage and collaborate with technology partners to enhance the overall technology architecture of the HQLAX platform for customers.<br/>• Participate in threat modelling, audits, due diligence, vendor risk assessments and other risk-related activities.<br/>• Coordinate and participate in penetration tests and disaster recovery tests.<br/>• Cover part of an on-call rota to provide production support.</p><h3>Qualifications</h3><p>‍<br/>• Master’s Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, or related field. We specifically expect up-to-date knowledge in these areas: networking, relational databases, security.<br/>• Solid grasp of modern software development practices (version control, continuous integration/delivery, acceptance testing, etc.). Significant hands-on experience in the fields of software development and operations.<br/>• A self-starter attitude and willingness to roll up your sleeves to help HQLAX achieve its goals.<br/>• Strong interpersonal and communication skills, including a strong command of English, both written and spoken.</p><p>• Strong coordination and communication skills to effectively coordinate test activities across stakeholders, partners, contractors, and vendors.<br/>• Strong organizational skills and a structured work methodology in all tasks and projects<br/>• Good understanding of the operational and security requirements that come with operating in a regulated, financial environment.<br/>• Knowledge of SOC2, ISO27001 or other related standards is a plus.<br/>• Knowledge of blockchain principles is a plus but not essential.<br/>• Hands-on, multiyear experience in the following areas:<br/>▪ Unix/Linux: installing, configuring and troubleshooting Unix/Linux-based environments, preferably for a financial services institution.<br/>▪ Networking: (TCP/IP, firewalls, load balancers, proxy configuration)<br/>▪ Security: key management, HSMs, PKI, TLS, VPNs, Single Sign-On, vulnerability management, penetration testing.<br/>▪ Databases: database administration, SQL, Oracle experience is a plus.<br/>▪ Cloud: automated management of secure, stable, test and production environments (using Ansible, Chef, Puppet etc.); Azure experience is a plus.<br/>▪ Testing: creating test plans, coordinating tests, executing tests (acceptance, performance, load, security).<br/>▪ Message broker/steaming: Configuring and operating message brokers (RabbitMQ, ActiveMQ, etc.); and/or Message Streaming (Kafka, RedPanda, etc.)<br/>▪ Monitoring: using stacks such as ELK, Datadog, Graphite/Grafana, etc.<br/>▪ Scripting: Python, shell.<br/>▪ JVM: building, packaging, distributing, deploying, tuning, and monitoring of JVM-based application stacks.<br/>▪ Version Control: git<br/>▪ Incident management and incident response.<br/>▪ Using Atlassian tool set such as Confluence, Jira, Service Desk, etc.<br/>▪ Virtualization and containerization (i.e. Docker, Kubernetes).</p><p>‍</p><h3>What we offer</h3><p>A team of dynamic and energetic professionals within a challenging and knowledge sharing environment. • Technical challenges unique to the fintech industry. • An attractive and competitive benefits package. • Flexible work-from-home arrangements.<br/>HQLAᵡ is committed to building a diverse team. We encourage candidates of all different backgrounds and identities to apply.</p><p>‍</p><h3><strong>Interested in this role?</strong> </h3><p>‍</p><p>Please apply in English at <a href="mailto:careers@hqla-x.com">careers@hqla-x.com</a></p><p>HQLA<sup>X</sup> is committed to building a diverse team. We encourage candidates of all different backgrounds and identities to apply.</p><p>‍</p><p>‍</p><p>‍</p><p>‍</p></div><div class="newsauthorsec"><img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/647085cadeace073b850ba3c/647d883df7de8d62ea284e2b_quote.svg" loading="lazy" alt="" class="image-22 w-condition-invisible"/><div class="authorinner"><div class="text-block-56 w-dyn-bind-empty"></div><div class="authorsubinner"><img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/647085cadeace073b850ba3c/647d89e1b2a2a4d5c6652e42_Line%2018.svg" loading="lazy" alt="" class="image-23 w-condition-invisible"/><div><div class="text-block-57 w-dyn-bind-empty"></div><div class="text-block-58 w-dyn-bind-empty"></div></div></div></div></div><div clas